Barcelona appears to be returning to their winning ways in the Spanish league after handing arch rivals, Real Madrid, a humiliating 4-0 defeat on Sunday. Barcelona’s new buy from Arsenal, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, hit the net twice in the match played at the Santiago Bernabeu.
The victory proved the improvement of the team being coached by Xavi Hernandez.  They are building up strongly for the 2023 La Liga season, having lost out of the 2022 champions league contest earlier and currently playing in the Europa competition.
Meanwhile, the coach of Barcelona, Xavi Hernandez, had said that the doors are wide open for Lionel Messi to return to the club. Messi appears to be unhappy at PSG of France.
 
